      <p class="apn-s-section-label">The Stack</p>
      <h2 class="apn-s-headline">What Actually Moves the Needle for Stress</h2>
      <div class="apn-s-divider"></div>

      <p class="apn-s-body">Supplements are the final variable in a closed system. They amplify what your protocol already built. The protocol in Module 4 is 80% of this result. The stack below makes the remaining 20% precise.</p>

      <!-- PRIMARY: Adapt -->
      <div class="apn-s-product-card">
        <p class="apn-s-product-name">Primary Supplement</p>
        <p class="apn-s-product-title">Adapt — Ashwagandha KSM-66</p>
        <p class="apn-s-product-price">$14.99 | Stress and Recovery Support</p>

        <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">The Mechanism</p>
        <p class="apn-s-product-detail">Adapt uses KSM-66, the most clinically studied form of ashwagandha. Withanolides, the active compounds in KSM-66, act on the HPA axis by modulating CRH receptor sensitivity and reducing adrenal output of cortisol. In a double-blind, placebo-controlled trial at 600mg daily for 8 weeks, participants showed a 27.9% reduction in serum cortisol and a 17% increase in testosterone. The mechanism is HPA axis normalization, not sedation. You will not feel groggy. You will recover harder.</p>

        <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">Dose and Timing</p>
        <p class="apn-s-product-detail">600mg daily. Take with dinner. Evening timing is deliberate: cortisol has its natural nadir in the late evening, and ashwagandha's effect on cortisol output is amplified when the adrenal glands are already trending toward lower output. Taking it at night accelerates the downward cortisol curve and protects the growth hormone pulse during early slow-wave sleep.</p>

        <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">Synergy</p>
        <p class="apn-s-product-detail">Pairs directly with Function (Magnesium Glycinate). Ashwagandha reduces cortisol output via the HPA axis. Magnesium reduces HPA axis reactivity at the neural level. They work on the same system through different mechanisms, which means the combined effect is additive.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- SECONDARY: Function (all tiers) -->
      <div class="apn-s-product-card">
        <p class="apn-s-product-name">Secondary Supplement</p>
        <p class="apn-s-product-title">Function — Magnesium Glycinate</p>
        <p class="apn-s-product-price">$19.99 | Recovery and Sleep Support</p>

        <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">The Mechanism</p>
        <p class="apn-s-product-detail">Magnesium deficiency is estimated to affect over 50% of athletes, and deficiency directly amplifies HPA axis reactivity. Magnesium regulates NMDA receptors in the hypothalamus that control CRH release. When magnesium is low, the HPA axis fires more easily and recovers more slowly from stress stimuli. Magnesium glycinate specifically: the glycinate chelation improves absorption significantly compared to magnesium oxide and reduces the GI side effects common with magnesium citrate at higher doses. Glycine itself also activates inhibitory glycine receptors in the central nervous system, producing an independent calming effect.</p>

        <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">Dose and Timing</p>
        <p class="apn-s-product-detail">400mg elemental magnesium as magnesium glycinate. Take 30 to 60 minutes before bed. Magnesium reduces sleep onset latency by an average of 17 minutes in clinical studies, and the mechanism is GABA-ergic: magnesium potentiates GABA receptor activity, reducing central nervous system excitability ahead of sleep.</p>

        <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">Synergy</p>
        <p class="apn-s-product-detail">The magnesium-ashwagandha combination addresses the HPA axis from two angles. Ashwagandha reduces the amplitude of the cortisol response. Magnesium reduces the threshold of HPA axis activation. Together, your stress response system fires less often and recovers faster when it does fire.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- TERTIARY: Balance (Athlete, Elite, Champion) -->
      <div class="apn-tier-block" data-tier="athlete">
        <div class="apn-s-product-card">
          <p class="apn-s-product-name">Tertiary Supplement</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-title">Balance — Platinum Turmeric</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-price">$19.99 | Inflammation Support</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">The Mechanism</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">Chronic cortisol elevation drives sustained low-grade inflammation through NF-kB pathway activation and increased pro-inflammatory cytokine expression (IL-6, TNF-alpha). Curcumin, the active compound in turmeric, is a direct NF-kB inhibitor. It blocks the transcription factor that drives the downstream inflammatory cascade from chronic HPA axis activation. This is not primary cortisol management. It is downstream inflammation management from the cortisol you are already working to reduce.</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">Dose and Timing</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">500mg curcumin. Take with your largest meal, which contains dietary fat. Curcumin is fat-soluble and poorly absorbed without fat. The product includes black pepper extract (piperine), which inhibits curcumin glucuronidation in the gut and liver, increasing bioavailability by up to 2,000%.</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">Synergy</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">Works downstream of Adapt and Function. Ashwagandha and magnesium reduce cortisol output. Balance manages the inflammatory byproduct of the cortisol that does get produced. Stack in this order of priority.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="apn-tier-block" data-tier="elite">
        <div class="apn-s-product-card">
          <p class="apn-s-product-name">Tertiary Supplement</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-title">Balance — Platinum Turmeric</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-price">$19.99 | Inflammation Support</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">The Mechanism</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">Chronic cortisol elevation drives sustained low-grade inflammation through NF-kB pathway activation and increased pro-inflammatory cytokine expression (IL-6, TNF-alpha). Curcumin, the active compound in turmeric, is a direct NF-kB inhibitor. It blocks the transcription factor that drives the downstream inflammatory cascade from chronic HPA axis activation.</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">Dose and Timing</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">500mg curcumin with your largest fat-containing meal. The product includes black pepper extract (piperine) for bioavailability. Take consistently, not situationally. Anti-inflammatory compounds work through chronic receptor modulation, not acute spikes.</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">Synergy</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">Works downstream of Adapt and Function to address the inflammatory consequence of HPA axis dysregulation. At the Elite tier, stack all three with the Omega-3 addition below for full-spectrum cortisol and inflammation management.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="apn-tier-block" data-tier="champion">
        <div class="apn-s-product-card">
          <p class="apn-s-product-name">Tertiary Supplement</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-title">Balance — Platinum Turmeric</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-price">$19.99 | Inflammation Support</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">The Mechanism</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">Chronic cortisol elevation drives sustained low-grade inflammation through NF-kB pathway activation. Curcumin is a direct NF-kB inhibitor. At the Champion tier, this is a maintenance tool. Consistent use prevents the inflammatory accumulation that compounds over training seasons.</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">Dose and Timing</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">500mg curcumin with your largest fat-containing meal. Non-negotiable. Do not cycle this product on and off. Chronic NF-kB suppression requires consistent dosing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FOURTH: Omega-3 (Athlete+) -->
      <div class="apn-tier-block" data-tier="athlete">
        <div class="apn-s-product-card">
          <p class="apn-s-product-name">Fourth Supplement</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-title">Omega-3</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-price">$24.99 | Cortisol and Inflammation Support</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">The Mechanism</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">EPA (eicosapentaenoic acid) directly reduces the cortisol response to psychological stress. The mechanism involves EPA's effect on HPA axis reactivity and its role in reducing sympathetic nervous system tone. Higher omega-3 index has been correlated with lower salivary cortisol response to acute stressors in controlled trials. DHA supports hippocampal function, which is the brain region responsible for HPA axis negative feedback. A well-functioning hippocampus tells the HPA axis to turn off. DHA deficiency impairs this feedback loop.</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">Dose and Timing</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">2 to 3g combined EPA and DHA daily. Take with a fat-containing meal for optimal absorption. If split dosing, morning and evening both work. Prioritize hitting the EPA threshold (minimum 1g EPA daily) for the cortisol-specific effect.</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">Synergy</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">At the Athlete tier and above, the full stack operates as a system: Adapt reduces cortisol output, Function reduces HPA axis reactivity, Balance manages downstream inflammation, and Omega-3 reduces the cortisol response amplitude to new stress inputs. Each layer addresses a different point in the stress cascade.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="apn-tier-block" data-tier="elite">
        <div class="apn-s-product-card">
          <p class="apn-s-product-name">Fourth Supplement</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-title">Omega-3</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-price">$24.99 | Cortisol and Inflammation Support</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">The Mechanism</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">EPA directly reduces the cortisol response to psychological stress. DHA supports hippocampal negative feedback on the HPA axis. At 3g combined EPA/DHA daily, the cortisol blunting effect is measurable in controlled conditions within 4 to 6 weeks of consistent use.</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">Dose and Timing</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">3g combined EPA and DHA daily. Minimum 1.5g EPA for the cortisol-specific effect. Take with food. Check the label for EPA/DHA split: not all fish oil products deliver the EPA content the dose implies.</p>
