          <p class="apn-s-product-name">Fourth Supplement</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-title">Omega-3</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-price">$24.99 | Cortisol and Inflammation Support</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">The Mechanism</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">EPA reduces HPA axis reactivity. DHA maintains hippocampal negative feedback. At the Champion tier, Omega-3 is a longevity and maintenance tool. Consistent use keeps HPA axis sensitivity calibrated over multi-year training blocks. This is not optional at your level.</p>

          <p class="apn-s-product-detail-label">Dose and Timing</p>
          <p class="apn-s-product-detail">3g combined EPA and DHA daily. Non-negotiable. Every day. With food.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="apn-s-warning">
        <p class="apn-s-warning-label">Common Stack Mistake</p>
        <p>Taking ashwagandha in the morning. The common rationale is "it reduces cortisol, which is highest in the morning, so take it then." This is backwards. Morning cortisol elevation is the cortisol awakening response (CAR), which is a normal and adaptive function. Suppressing it in the morning impairs alertness and focus. The target is evening cortisol, which should decline. Evening dosing with dinner is correct. Morning dosing is the mistake.</p>
